Lets start with ANDROID STUDIO
Hope u have installed it...
we are going to create an android virtual device(android emulator) to check our output
steps:
1. open the app you will find configure in the right bottom select AVD MANAGER option there.
2.we have to choose a device . I choose nexas 6 here.->next
3.we will choose the system image->pie(operation system)->next -> u can name-> emulated performance->graphics->harware(glsi)-> finish
Your virtual device is installed.
we will install some plugins..
1)settings-> plugings->marketplace->Flutter(dart installed automatically)->yes->restart ide
Then we can see flutter application written on the main screen ->click that->flutter application->next->next->finish
Hurray we got the screen for Flutter app...
